{A DAY IN THE LIFE OF A FARMER {continued
At 12.30 Mr.Enderle has his hard earned dinner which he takes nearly an hour to eat.After dinner Mr.Enderle takes his daughter Merie to the primary school.He gets back around 12.40.Most of the afternoon Mr.Enderle just does odd jobs around the farm like hay-bailing,and feeding the bullocks.At 3.30 Mr.Enderle goes back into Holsworthy to pick up Merie.He gets back to the farm at 3.45 and from then until 5.00 Mr.Enderle does odd jobs.At 5.10 Mr.Enderle has his tea.At 6.00 Mr.Enderle goes to the pub and he stays there until 8.OO.Then he watches T.V. until 1.00 when he goes to bed.
{by James McGuire,Charles Enderle { and Ian Brown }
